to what extent are we really

00:39:09.690 --> 00:39:12.550
looking at the people who
are much better off going

00:39:12.550 --> 00:39:15.830
in systematically taking the
land, as you were saying,

00:39:15.830 --> 00:39:17.980
from the poor and
enslaving the poor and so

00:39:17.980 --> 00:39:20.520
forth, as opposed to domestic
violence, which might be more

00:39:20.520 --> 00:39:22.220
of a poor-on-poor
or kind of thing.

00:39:22.220 --> 00:39:23.220
GARY HAUGEN: Yeah.

00:39:23.220 --> 00:39:25.640
It's both.

00:39:25.640 --> 00:39:33.431
Poor-on-poor violence is sort of
 relatively-poor-against-the-poorest

00:39:33.431 --> 00:39:33.930
violence.

00:39:33.930 --> 00:39:34.429
Right?

00:39:34.429 --> 00:39:36.160
So the opening
