00:48:17.210 --> 00:48:18.960
Because the legal
institutions were set up

00:48:18.960 --> 00:48:21.710
by the colonial powers, and they
have never been re-engineered.

00:48:21.710 --> 00:48:23.840
This is the other amazing thing.

00:48:23.840 --> 00:48:25.830
The laws have changed?

00:48:25.830 --> 00:48:27.820
Post-colonial
wonderful embedding

00:48:27.820 --> 00:48:32.370
of human rights standards
in domestic law.

00:48:32.370 --> 00:48:34.910
But the pipeline that
actually delivers those rights

00:48:34.910 --> 00:48:38.810
is law enforcement, which has
been set up by a colonial model

00:48:38.810 --> 00:48:40.360
and never changed.

00:48:40.360 --> 00:48:44.650
And so one of the
things that manifests

00:48:44.650 --> 00:48:48.400
is that you don't have
any representation at all.

00:48:48.400 --> 00:48:50.040
And you do it in a
proceeding that's

00:48:50.040 --> 00:48:53.430
conducted in a language
you don't understand.

00:48:53.430 --> 00:48:56.450
So imagine, you're
accused of a crime.

00:48:56.450 --> 00:48:58.440
You are thrown into a
proceeding in which you

00:48:58.440 --> 00:49:00.140
have no legal protection.

00:49:00.140 --> 00:49:02.620
And you can't understand a word.

00:49:02.620 --> 00:49:04.920
And then you just get
shuffled off to jail.

00:49:04.920 --> 00:49:06.640
And you're sort of
asking, as I see

00:49:06.640 --> 00:49:09.440
this many times, the
defendant who's poor,

00:49:09.440 --> 00:49:12.360
asking the guard, of course,
who has no education,

00:49:12.360 --> 00:49:14.860
is illiterate generally,
but to ask the guard,

00:49:14.860 --> 00:49:17.770
can you just please
explain what just happened?

00:49:17.770 --> 00:49:21.349
So ever society needs
to carry vigilance

00:49:21.349 --> 00:49:23.640
on behalf of those who are
poorest and most vulnerable,

00:49:23.640 --> 00:49:27.300
who are going to get run over
by a criminal justice system,

00:49:27.300 --> 00:49:30.810
But the utter collapse of these
systems in the developing world

00:49:30.810 --> 00:49:34.120
is something, as we
wrote in another article,

00:49:34.120 --> 00:49:35.620
you almost have
to see to believe.

00:49:35.620 --> 00:49:38.369
And we're hoping to just
bring that to the surface.

00:49:38.369 --> 00:49:38.910
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:49:38.910 --> 00:49:42.400
I was just curious if you
had any thoughts on any ways

00:49:42.400 --> 00:49:46.630
that information technology has
impacted this problem at all.

00:49:46.630 --> 00:49:48.179
Have you seen this
through your work?

00:49:48.179 --> 00:49:49.845
Are there things that
we could be doing?

00:49:49.845 --> 00:49:53.777
You know, a big place like
Google-- that could help.

00:49:53.777 --> 00:49:54.860
GARY HAUGEN: Massively so.

00:49:54.860 --> 00:49:58.360
And in fact, we have
had some opportunities

00:49:58.360 --> 00:50:01.270
to bring out our director
of investigations,

00:50:01.270 --> 00:50:04.360
for example, who was
formerly the director of NCIS

00:50:04.360 --> 00:50:07.130
to talk about the amazing ways
that actually technology can be

00:50:07.130 --> 00:50:09.990
leveraged in on
behalf of the poor

00:50:09.990 --> 00:50:11.720
to fight much of this crime.

00:50:11.720 --> 00:50:13.960
In many ways in the
developing world,

00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:16.640
these technological
advances are leapfrogging

00:50:16.640 --> 00:50:19.600
in ways that are able to
empower the poor tremendously.

00:50:19.600 --> 00:50:23.010
When I started doing this
work, there-- I know,

00:50:23.010 --> 00:50:25.280
it's dating me a bit, but
there were no cell phones

00:50:25.280 --> 00:50:26.400
in the developing world.

00:50:26.400 --> 00:50:30.790
And now we give cell phones to
slaves inside brick factories.

00:50:30.790 --> 00:50:33.230
And they are able to
communicate with us.

00:50:33.230 --> 00:50:37.410
And then there's
using imagery to find

00:50:37.410 --> 00:50:42.530
places that are more likely
to be using slave labor,

00:50:42.530 --> 00:50:44.960
the way of creating
sort of hot spots

00:50:44.960 --> 00:50:48.030
where abuse is
taking through data.

00:50:48.030 --> 00:50:50.230
The truth is though
every word I just

00:50:50.230 --> 00:50:52.740
used I was acting like I knew
what I was talking about.

00:50:52.740 --> 00:50:53.960
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:53.960 --> 00:50:56.250
GARY HAUGEN: You guys are
more likely to be the ones

00:50:56.250 --> 00:50:58.740
to actually get
to know the needs,

00:50:58.740 --> 00:51:01.790
and then to begin to dream and
imagine what technology can do.

00:51:01.790 --> 00:51:04.090
So that would be another
wonderful thing for you guys

00:51:04.090 --> 00:51:06.980
to read the book, acquaint
yourself with the problems,

00:51:06.980 --> 00:51:09.660
and then begin to imagine with
us the way in which technology

00:51:09.660 --> 00:51:10.800
can be leveraged.

00:51:10.800 --> 00:51:13.340
Because one of just absolute
things that technology

00:51:13.340 --> 00:51:17.450
is able to do is to bring
transparency to what's

00:51:17.450 --> 00:51:20.810
happening by empowering people
to signal what is happening

00:51:20.810 --> 00:51:23.445
or communicate what's happening
and to shrink the world

00:51:23.445 --> 00:51:25.410
and to do it to do it real time.

00:51:25.410 --> 00:51:27.510
I think technology is
fundamentally just going

00:51:27.510 --> 00:51:29.135
to make it harder
and harder and harder

00:51:29.135 --> 00:51:30.690
to get away with these things.

00:51:30.690 --> 00:51:33.210
And that is what the victims
of abuse and violence

00:51:33.210 --> 00:51:36.870
need most is for other
people to know about it.

00:51:36.870 --> 00:51:39.390
Because if you think about it,
what does a violent criminal

00:51:39.390 --> 00:51:39.890
always do?

00:51:39.890 --> 00:51:42.510
And its part of the thing
that makes them so scary

00:51:42.510 --> 00:51:45.450
is they hide what
they do in the dark.

00:51:45.450 --> 00:51:48.750
And they try to intimidate
other people from seeing it.

00:51:48.750 --> 00:51:50.500
Why do they do that?

00:51:50.500 --> 00:51:52.840
They do it because
they're afraid.

00:51:52.840 --> 00:51:54.660
Criminals are
fundamentally afraid,

00:51:54.660 --> 00:51:56.859
that if other people
know what's going on,

00:51:56.859 --> 00:51:58.900
they won't be able to
withstand the power that we

00:51:58.900 --> 00:52:00.191
brought to bear upon the theme.

00:52:00.191 --> 00:52:04.160
So that way the technology can
bring us much more to actually

00:52:04.160 --> 00:52:06.790
be transparent about what's
going on in the world

00:52:06.790 --> 00:52:09.227
and empower even the weakest
to be able to do that.

00:52:09.227 --> 00:52:11.810
I think we're going to be living
in a very different and safer

00:52:11.810 --> 00:52:12.605
world for the poor.

00:52:12.605 --> 00:52:14.480
PAUL LEE: Just join me
in giving Gary a hand.

00:52:14.480 --> 00:52:17.530
Thanks for coming
over, appreciate it.

